  "prompt": "How to get more RP (free) than 400 in LoL?",
  "response": "Increasing your RP (Riot Points) in League of Legends without spending money is limited since RP is typically obtained through purchases. However, there are several ways to earn additional rewards and in-game currency that can indirectly help you achieve your goals. Here are some methods to maximize your RP and overall rewards:\n\n1. **Participate in Events and Missions**: Riot Games often hosts events that come with missions. Completing these can sometimes reward you with free RP or in-game currency.\n\n2. **Play the Game**: While you can't earn RP directly from games, participating in regular play can earn you Blue Essence, which can be used for in-game purchases.\n\n3. **Refer Friends**: The Refer a Friend program allows you to earn rewards if your friends join and play League of Legends. Keep an eye out for any referral events that might reward you with RP.\n\n4. **Giveaways and Promotions**: Occasionally, streamers or community events will host giveaways that include RP. Engaging with the community on platforms like Twitch, Twitter, or Reddit can provide you opportunities to win RP.\n\n5. **Game Sales and Promotions**: Sometimes, Riot offers discounts or promotions that might allow you to maximize the value of your RP. Keep an eye out for sales events that may coincide with major updates or seasons.\n\n6. **Feedback and Surveys**: Riot sometimes conducts surveys that reward players with in-game currency for their feedback. Participating in these can occasionally yield bonuses.\n\n7. **Earn Rewards through Tournaments or Competitions**: If you're skilled at the game, you can look for community-run tournaments or competitions with RP prizes.\n\nRemember, RP is primarily a paid currency, and these methods may not yield a large amount. It is always wise to be cautious about spending and to enjoy the game at your own pace!",
